pull_request.title: Update Chromium build instructions
pull_request.body:
* Add instructions to build Chromium on Windows
  - Add QUIC support to the OQS-Chromium (currently quantum safe KEX cannot be used with QUIC on OQS-Chromium)
  - Add quantum safe signature support to QOS-Chromium (solve issue #111 )
* A prebuilt 64-bit Windows Chromium installer can be found [here](https://filebin.net/vjpj3eo13yb3tes2). Note: oqstest_CA is hard coded into the source code of this Chromium

pull_request.title: README correction to docs path & additional gitignore to macos + vscode
pull_request.body:
<!-- Please give a brief explanation of the purpose of this pull request. -->
1. Add common macOS filetype to .gitignore to avoid accidental checkins
2. Add visual studio code / jetbrains IDE config file location to .gitignore as above
3. Correction to readme - path to generated documentation was incorrect

Both are very minor, but things I noticed when using liboqs for the first time, and walking through the documentation.
Hope this really small contribution helps & is appropriate.

I can also squash or re-edit to follow appropriate guidelines if needed

<!-- Does this PR resolve any issue?  If so, please reference it using automatic-closing keywords like "Fixes #123." -->

<!-- Please answer the following questions to help manage version and changes across projects. -->

* [x] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.) **-> NO**
* [x] Does this PR change the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming? Does this PR otherwise change an API? (If so, PRs in [oqs-provider](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-provider), [OQS-OpenSSL](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl), [OQS-BoringSSL](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/boringssl), and [OQS-OpenSSH](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssh) will also need to be ready for review and merge by the time this is merged.) **-> NO**

<!-- Once your pull request is ready for review and passing continuous integration tests, please convert from a draft PR to a normal PR, and request a review from one of the OQS core team members. -->

No tests executed - this is just a Readme & .gitignore update
